      "decision": "In-process model serving over dedicated model server (e.g., TF Serving, Triton)",
      "gains": "Eliminates network hop (saves 5-15ms at P99). Simpler deployment — one service to operate. Matches team size.",
      "sacrifices": "Model and API are deployed together (though hot-swap mitigates this). Harder to serve multiple model types simultaneously.",
      "alternatives_considered": ["TF Serving / Triton — rejected: adds operational complexity, network latency, and another service to maintain for a 4-person team", "ONNX Runtime sidecar — considered: viable but unnecessary complexity for LightGBM"]
